
1) Pull Fedora based ssh image(available in Dockerfile)
2) run single / multiple instances
	docker run -d --name test-ssh -p 2200:22 -e SSH_USER=mrajaa -e SSH_USERPASS=mrajaa mukuntharajaa/ssh
3) ssh -p 2200 mrajaa@localhost

	Here we can not use ip of container(yet to figure out why)
	Use either localhost or ip address of docker host

	More useful reading at,

	
4) I am mainly using this container for simulating ansible nodes
